The paper deals with the problem of link prediction in dynamic networks, which involves understanding the temporal dynamics of a complex system such as a social network or a communication network. This problem is relevant to several sub-fields of computer science, including social network analysis (cs.SI), machine learning (cs.LG), data mining (cs.DS), and systems and control (cs.SY). Additionally, the paper proposes a novel method for metric embedding of node-pair instances of a dynamic network, which could be relevant to the sub-field of statistical learning theory (cs.SD).
